WEBVTT

00:00:07.474 --> 00:00:08.909
(Blue Girl)
Akira's counting on me

00:00:08.943 --> 00:00:12.312
to bring back an ignis
and I won't let him down,

00:00:12.312 --> 00:00:16.784
and I won't let myself down
by not giving it my all.

00:00:16.817 --> 00:00:19.753
Alright, Soulburner,
just because you two

00:00:19.787 --> 00:00:22.923
are buds with Playmaker doesn't
mean I'll go easy on you.

00:00:22.957 --> 00:00:25.492
(Soulburner)
Yeah, we never
expected you would

00:00:25.492 --> 00:00:27.193
but thanks for the
warning anyway.

00:00:28.762 --> 00:00:31.965
Blue Girl is looking
tough and I like it.

00:00:31.999 --> 00:00:34.034
(Blue girl)
I rebuilt my deck from scratch

00:00:34.101 --> 00:00:35.435
to plug up the
holes in my strategy

00:00:35.469 --> 00:00:37.805
and now is the time
to put it to the test.

00:00:37.805 --> 00:00:40.006
You ready to duel Soulburner?

00:00:40.073 --> 00:00:41.942
(Flame)
According to
my dueling logs,

00:00:41.976 --> 00:00:44.611
Blue Girl uses combos
to slowly whittle

00:00:44.644 --> 00:00:47.480
her opponents life points
all the way down to zero.

00:00:47.480 --> 00:00:50.184
I heard, so then
we'd better not let

00:00:50.251 --> 00:00:51.318
her do that
to us, Flame.

00:00:51.318 --> 00:00:52.352
(Flame)
Agreed.

00:00:52.419 --> 00:00:54.254
We've gotta be sure
to set up our counter strategies

00:00:54.288 --> 00:00:56.090
before she can
start her combo,

00:00:56.123 --> 00:00:58.925
meaning we need to be the
ones to go first in this duel.

00:01:02.396 --> 00:01:05.398
Blue Girl, how about
whoever goes underneath

00:01:05.432 --> 00:01:08.402
that arch first gets to
go first in our duel,

00:01:08.469 --> 00:01:09.503
we got a deal?

00:01:09.536 --> 00:01:10.670
Yeah, deal.

00:01:34.394 --> 00:01:35.395
I win.

00:01:38.833 --> 00:01:40.767
So I get to go first.

00:01:42.402 --> 00:01:45.338
(Flame)
Oh byte, that's the
last thing we wanted.

00:02:47.133 --> 00:02:49.236
(Both)
It's time to speed duel.

00:02:51.104 --> 00:02:54.275
Here I go, I'll
start by activating

00:02:54.275 --> 00:02:56.543
my spell, Trickstar Vision.

00:02:56.576 --> 00:02:59.446
It lets me summon
Trickstar Lilybell.

00:03:00.414 --> 00:03:02.850
(Aqua)
In addition, both players
draw one card

00:03:02.883 --> 00:03:05.019
but Lilybell's attack
point are cut in half

00:03:05.052 --> 00:03:07.121
and she loses her
special abilities.

00:03:07.154 --> 00:03:09.789
(Blue girl)
You know, I never realized
you were such a downer.

00:03:10.691 --> 00:03:11.825
You get to draw as well.

00:03:12.359 --> 00:03:13.293
Okay.

00:03:15.962 --> 00:03:18.132
Next, I can summon
Trickstar Lycoris

00:03:18.165 --> 00:03:20.901
by returning a Trickstar
on my field to my hand.

00:03:22.269 --> 00:03:24.337
Come on back,
Trickstar Lilybell.

00:03:25.705 --> 00:03:27.775
But she won't be gone for long.

00:03:27.775 --> 00:03:30.477
Her special ability
automatically resummons

00:03:30.510 --> 00:03:31.511
her to the field.

00:03:34.014 --> 00:03:37.183
And I'll now use her
to build my circus.

00:03:38.786 --> 00:03:42.622
I set Trickstar Lilybell and
Lycoris in the Link Arrow,

00:03:43.824 --> 00:03:47.727
I link summon link-2
Trickstar Divaridis.

00:03:50.964 --> 00:03:52.833
When I summon Divaridis,

00:03:52.866 --> 00:03:56.102
her special ability deals
you 200 points of damage.

00:04:01.342 --> 00:04:04.044
I know 200 wasn't much

00:04:04.077 --> 00:04:06.246
but trust that it'll
sting a mighty ton

00:04:06.279 --> 00:04:08.615
when I get the
damage snowballing.

00:04:08.682 --> 00:04:11.552
I activate my field spell,
Trickstar Live Stage,

00:04:11.585 --> 00:04:14.588
to return a Trickstar in
my graveyard to my hand,

00:04:14.622 --> 00:04:16.423
like my Trickstar Lycoris,

00:04:20.060 --> 00:04:22.362
and Trickstar Live Stage
has another effect.

00:04:23.363 --> 00:04:25.966
When I have a Trickstar
Link monster on my field,

00:04:26.033 --> 00:04:28.369
I'm allowed to summon
a Trickstar Token next

00:04:28.402 --> 00:04:29.870
to her Link Arrow,

00:04:32.706 --> 00:04:34.207
and I'm tributing this token

00:04:34.241 --> 00:04:37.678
to summon a brand new Trickstar.

00:04:37.711 --> 00:04:39.546
Trickstar Birdhelm,

00:04:41.082 --> 00:04:42.449
and whenever I'm able

00:04:42.516 --> 00:04:44.184
to successfully summon her,

00:04:44.184 --> 00:04:47.354
her special ability deals
you 200 points of damage.

00:04:50.024 --> 00:04:51.625
Plus I get
to draw a card.

00:04:53.860 --> 00:04:56.129
Unfortunately, my
Birdhelm can't attack

00:04:56.196 --> 00:04:57.731
when she uses this ability.

00:04:57.764 --> 00:05:00.033
(Flame)
How is it unfortunate
when you're not allowed

00:05:00.033 --> 00:05:02.236
to attack on the
first turn anyway?

00:05:02.236 --> 00:05:03.971
Hello, because I
was kidding but here's

00:05:04.004 --> 00:05:07.274
what's not unfortunate.
I can resummon Lycoris again

00:05:07.308 --> 00:05:09.743
by returning
Birdhelm to my hand.

00:05:11.912 --> 00:05:14.081
This is great, she's
comboing her combos

00:05:14.081 --> 00:05:15.483
just like I was afraid of.

00:05:15.516 --> 00:05:18.018
Now I activate
Birdhelm's special ability.

00:05:19.853 --> 00:05:22.456
She transforms
into an equip card

00:05:22.490 --> 00:05:25.659
and I equip her onto
Trickstar Divaridis.

00:05:28.595 --> 00:05:31.431
It's your turn,
show me what you got.

00:05:32.599 --> 00:05:35.236
Be careful what you
wish for, Blue Gal.

00:05:35.403 --> 00:05:36.504
Why?

00:05:36.570 --> 00:05:39.072
You're not in control of this
duel and you never will be,

00:05:39.072 --> 00:05:41.741
not even when it's
your turn, Soulburner.

00:05:44.244 --> 00:05:46.913
You're not in control of this
duel and you never will be,

00:05:46.913 --> 00:05:49.582
not even when it's
your turn, Soulburner.

00:05:49.582 --> 00:05:51.518
Whenever you add a
card to your hand,

00:05:51.585 --> 00:05:54.087
Lycoris deals you
200 points of damage.

00:05:59.192 --> 00:06:00.594
I'm taking all
this damage just

00:06:00.627 --> 00:06:02.529
because I couldn't
go first.

00:06:02.563 --> 00:06:04.197
(Flame)
Perhaps Soulburner
should've invested

00:06:04.231 --> 00:06:06.667
in afterburners
for his duel board.

00:06:06.700 --> 00:06:09.804
See, just as you did
your research on me,

00:06:09.804 --> 00:06:11.404
I studied up on you.

00:06:11.471 --> 00:06:13.407
Such as, your
skill Burning Draw,

00:06:13.474 --> 00:06:15.141
which lets you draw
cards by lowering

00:06:15.175 --> 00:06:17.044
your life points to a hundred.

00:06:17.077 --> 00:06:18.312
But if I draw a card,

00:06:18.312 --> 00:06:21.081
your Lycoris will
deal me 200 damage.

00:06:21.148 --> 00:06:22.816
Yep, that's correct.

00:06:22.849 --> 00:06:25.820
(Flame)
So if we use our skill,
we will immediately lose.

00:06:25.853 --> 00:06:28.422
That is a clever way
to limit our options.

00:06:28.488 --> 00:06:30.691
But there's still
plenty that we can do.

00:06:30.724 --> 00:06:33.326
By sending Salamangreat
Falco to the graveyard,

00:06:33.326 --> 00:06:35.428
I can summon Salamangreat Meer.

00:06:38.399 --> 00:06:40.434
Yeah, but maybe
you shouldn't have

00:06:40.501 --> 00:06:42.802
because you triggered
Divaridis' ability.

00:06:42.802 --> 00:06:44.138
Each time you summon a monster,

00:06:44.138 --> 00:06:46.339
she dishes out 200
points of damage.

00:06:48.842 --> 00:06:51.645
(Soulburner)
Each hit hurts barely
more than a papercut

00:06:51.678 --> 00:06:53.814
but she keeps
slicing and slicing.

00:06:53.847 --> 00:06:55.849
I gotta destroy her
Trickstar Divaridis

00:06:55.882 --> 00:06:59.419
before the damage stacks
up and get outta control.

00:06:59.486 --> 00:07:02.889
I activate Salamangreat
Falco's special ability.

00:07:02.923 --> 00:07:05.959
I can now revive my Falco
by returning a Salamangreat

00:07:05.993 --> 00:07:08.729
on my field straight
back to my hand.

00:07:08.729 --> 00:07:11.831
So my Meer burrows back to make
way to make way for the sky.

00:07:15.602 --> 00:07:17.604
That one move of
yours triggered two

00:07:17.637 --> 00:07:19.773
of my monster's
special abilities.

00:07:19.806 --> 00:07:23.210
Lycoris and Divaridis
deal you 200 damage each.

00:07:24.945 --> 00:07:26.446
Well check this
next move out,

00:07:26.480 --> 00:07:28.715
if I add my Salamangreat
Meer to my hand

00:07:28.715 --> 00:07:29.883
without having
to draw it,

00:07:29.883 --> 00:07:31.251
I'm allowed
to resummon it.

00:07:34.722 --> 00:07:35.890
You sure talked
a whole lot

00:07:35.923 --> 00:07:38.492
but all I heard
was 200 damage.

00:07:38.558 --> 00:07:41.895
Yeah, yeah, yeah, next I
summon Salamangreat Wolvie.

00:07:44.632 --> 00:07:47.401
And by summoning that,
my Divaridis deals

00:07:47.401 --> 00:07:48.535
you damage again.

00:07:50.604 --> 00:07:53.373
(Blue girl)
There's only one reason
to do that.

00:07:53.373 --> 00:07:54.407
To link summon.

00:07:55.376 --> 00:07:57.377
(Flame)
Go Soulburner.

00:07:57.377 --> 00:08:00.213
Yeah, I blaze the
circuit that scorches

00:08:00.213 --> 00:08:02.782
the path to the future.

00:08:02.816 --> 00:08:04.451
The summoning conditions require

00:08:04.484 --> 00:08:06.620
at least two
fire-effect monsters.

00:08:06.620 --> 00:08:08.955
So I set all three in
of my Salamangreats

00:08:08.989 --> 00:08:10.624
in the Link Arrows.

00:08:13.127 --> 00:08:17.564
I link summon Link-3
Salamangreat Heatleo.

00:08:23.504 --> 00:08:26.774
Big cat but your kitty
just dragged 200 more points

00:08:26.774 --> 00:08:28.842
of damage right into
your living room.

00:08:31.344 --> 00:08:33.546
But now that I have
Heatleo, I can--

00:08:33.613 --> 00:08:34.882
Stop right there!

00:08:34.949 --> 00:08:36.717
I know you went through
all that trouble

00:08:36.784 --> 00:08:39.820
so you could use
Heatleo's ability but no.

00:08:39.853 --> 00:08:40.854
You knew?

00:08:40.888 --> 00:08:41.788
Yep.

00:08:41.822 --> 00:08:43.290
Your Heatleo can usually destroy

00:08:43.290 --> 00:08:44.792
my spell or trap card, right?

00:08:44.825 --> 00:08:46.893
But when Divaridis is
equipped with Birdhelm

00:08:46.960 --> 00:08:49.162
that ability gets shut down.

00:08:49.196 --> 00:08:52.166
(Flame)
She truly has prepared
for all our tactics.

00:08:52.199 --> 00:08:54.434
Yeah, but guess who
did their homework too.

00:08:56.436 --> 00:09:00.774
Heatleo, pounce and destroy
her Trickstar Divaridis.

00:09:00.841 --> 00:09:02.542
Every deck has their strengths

00:09:02.575 --> 00:09:04.211
but they also have
their weaknesses

00:09:04.244 --> 00:09:05.613
and I found yours.

00:09:05.679 --> 00:09:07.380
While your deck
has great combos,

00:09:07.414 --> 00:09:10.017
it doesn't have monsters
with a lot of attack points.

00:09:10.017 --> 00:09:13.353
So I can run you over
with sheer power.

00:09:13.386 --> 00:09:14.588
You're right.

00:09:14.622 --> 00:09:16.523
Well, you would've
been a few weeks ago,

00:09:18.192 --> 00:09:19.560
but you see I've been fixing

00:09:19.593 --> 00:09:21.795
the holes in my
game, Soulburner.

00:09:21.861 --> 00:09:23.897
By sending Trickstar
Calobane to the graveyard,

00:09:23.930 --> 00:09:26.367
Trickstar Divaridis'
attack points double

00:09:26.367 --> 00:09:27.667
until the end of the turn.

00:09:30.337 --> 00:09:31.571
That's crazy.

00:09:31.605 --> 00:09:33.173
Yeah, crazy awesome.

00:09:33.207 --> 00:09:35.208
She jumps to 3600 attack points

00:09:35.242 --> 00:09:38.178
which is more than plenty
to destroy Heatleo.

00:09:45.352 --> 00:09:48.054
Okay, well that didn't
work out too good.

00:09:48.088 --> 00:09:50.023
At least my Heatleo
is still alive.

00:09:51.058 --> 00:09:52.759
How?
Since I used

00:09:52.793 --> 00:09:54.761
my Salamangreat
Wolvie to summon it,

00:09:54.794 --> 00:09:58.031
its special ability protects
Heatleo from being destroyed

00:09:58.031 --> 00:09:59.633
and now I end my turn.

00:10:02.336 --> 00:10:03.570
We're behind the eight ball

00:10:03.604 --> 00:10:04.839
but at least we're still alive

00:10:04.872 --> 00:10:06.107
and as long as we're alive,

00:10:06.173 --> 00:10:07.674
we still have a chance.

00:10:12.212 --> 00:10:13.547
(Flame)
Hm, Soulburner?

00:10:13.580 --> 00:10:14.848
What's up there buddy?

00:10:14.848 --> 00:10:16.416
(Flame)
You only took one turn

00:10:16.416 --> 00:10:20.187
and you're already down
over 3000 life points.

00:10:20.220 --> 00:10:21.288
I know.

00:10:21.288 --> 00:10:23.390
(Flame)
So, I just wanted
to let you know

00:10:23.423 --> 00:10:26.526
that I find that impressive
in its own unique way.

00:10:26.526 --> 00:10:29.430
Weirdest pep talk I've ever
been a part of but whatever.

00:10:29.463 --> 00:10:31.198
(Flame)
No, you're
missing the point.

00:10:31.231 --> 00:10:33.367
What I'm saying is
that if we can recover

00:10:33.400 --> 00:10:36.671
from such a drastic downfall
and win it would be an even

00:10:36.704 --> 00:10:38.005
more impressive feat.

00:10:38.005 --> 00:10:40.674
Well yeah but are you
like, actually worried

00:10:40.707 --> 00:10:41.942
that we're going to lose?

00:10:42.009 --> 00:10:43.344
Why, of course not,

00:10:43.377 --> 00:10:47.080
because you have
me to help you.

00:10:47.114 --> 00:10:48.848
How could
I ever forget?

00:10:49.416 --> 00:10:50.751
It's my turn.

00:10:50.784 --> 00:10:52.019
I draw.

00:10:52.053 --> 00:10:55.289
I activate Trickstar
Live Stage's effect.

00:10:55.355 --> 00:10:56.790
(Aqua)
When the opponent

00:10:56.857 --> 00:10:59.292
has a face down spell or
trap card on their field,

00:10:59.359 --> 00:11:02.762
you are allowed to summon a
Trickstar Token in defense mode.

00:11:06.133 --> 00:11:07.767
And since my
Divaridis is equipped

00:11:07.767 --> 00:11:10.971
with Trickstar Birdhelm,
she can deal you 200 points

00:11:11.004 --> 00:11:14.407
of damage every time
I summon a Trickstar.

00:11:14.407 --> 00:11:17.611
(Flame)
So not only can she
deal damage when we summon.

00:11:17.644 --> 00:11:20.647
She can now deal damage
when she summons.

00:11:20.681 --> 00:11:23.250
She has elevated her
game, so we're running out

00:11:23.284 --> 00:11:25.586
of weaknesses to exploit.

00:11:25.619 --> 00:11:27.020
You're right, Flame,

00:11:27.087 --> 00:11:30.090
but all we need to find is
just one flaw to break through.

00:11:30.124 --> 00:11:31.292
(Flame)
Find a way.

00:11:31.325 --> 00:11:34.127
Maybe Gate of fire
will mess up her combo.

00:11:35.763 --> 00:11:38.198
I no longer take damage
outside of battle

00:11:38.265 --> 00:11:40.367
if it's less than 300 points.

00:11:40.434 --> 00:11:43.804
(Flame)
Ah, all her damage
is 200 each.

00:11:43.837 --> 00:11:46.807
Uh huh, so Blue Girl
won't be pinging me anymore.

00:11:46.841 --> 00:11:48.275
Really, is that so?

00:11:48.309 --> 00:11:50.810
But what if I used my
newest skill, Soulburner?

00:11:50.844 --> 00:11:52.579
Trickstar Gig.

00:11:52.612 --> 00:11:54.581
For every Trickstar
that's in play

00:11:54.615 --> 00:11:58.285
I send a card from the top
of my deck to the graveyard.

00:11:58.318 --> 00:12:01.355
So that means I'm gonna
be sending three cards.

00:12:01.389 --> 00:12:03.323
Yeah, I know this
sounds bad for me

00:12:05.692 --> 00:12:07.160
but its not because I get

00:12:07.160 --> 00:12:10.030
to retrieve one Trickstar
from my graveyard in exchange

00:12:10.064 --> 00:12:12.933
and this card here is
the perfect one for me.

00:12:15.469 --> 00:12:17.638
But there's a catch,
in order for me to play it

00:12:17.638 --> 00:12:19.540
I have to link summon first.

00:12:19.573 --> 00:12:23.376
So I'll build the circuit that
turns dreams into reality.

00:12:24.511 --> 00:12:26.846
The summoning conditions
are two Trickstars.

00:12:28.715 --> 00:12:32.419
Link summon, link-2
Trickstar Holly Angel.

00:12:36.990 --> 00:12:40.327
Then my field spell Trickstar
Live Stage activates

00:12:40.327 --> 00:12:44.231
to summon a Trickstar token
next to my link monster.

00:12:46.200 --> 00:12:49.470
Now I have what I need
to play my perfect card.

00:12:49.470 --> 00:12:52.572
I activate my spell,
Trickstar Fusion,

00:12:52.639 --> 00:12:54.675
it lets me fuse
my Trickstar token

00:12:54.708 --> 00:12:57.644
and Trickstar Holly
Angel together into one.

00:12:59.379 --> 00:13:03.150
Hey, Soulburner, when
you see my new Trickstar

00:13:03.217 --> 00:13:05.285
you'll be changing your tune.

00:13:07.821 --> 00:13:09.790
I fusion summon.

00:13:09.824 --> 00:13:13.093
Rock on, Trickstar
Band Sweet Guitar.

00:13:15.161 --> 00:13:17.564
She can play fusion monsters?

00:13:17.564 --> 00:13:19.566
(Flame)
It would seem so.

00:13:19.566 --> 00:13:21.601
It's another new
wrinkle to her game

00:13:21.635 --> 00:13:23.737
and another new headache for us.

